headline: S&P 500, Nasdaq rise with tech-related shares
summary: NEW YORK (Reuters) -The Nasdaq and S&P 500 rose on Monday along with tech-related shares after the market posted a strong November ahead of this week's economic data including the key monthly jobs report on Friday.  The Dow was down slightly on the day.  Both the Dow and S&P 500 recorded their best months in a year on Friday.

headline: Futures dip as caution prevails in data-packed week
summary: (Reuters) -U.S. stock index futures started December on a sour note after recording robust gains last month, with focus on a slew of economic data this week, including multiple labor market reports, to gauge the Federal Reserve's interest rate path.  "Strong data will certainly revive the rate-cut-or-not discussions, while soft numbers will boost appetite for another 25bp cut from the Fed," said Ipek Ozkardeskaya, senior analyst at Swissquote Bank.  Traders currently see a more than 65% chance of the Fed opting for a 25-basis-point rate cut when it meets later this month, compared to a near 83% chance seen a month prior, as per CME's FedWatch Tool, on the back of data pointing to a resilient economy.
